# Final check for density and connectivity:
# All Resources are linked to Applications, ProductModels, Loci, and managed by Agents.
# All NetworkInterfaces are linked to Resources and NetworkLinks.
# All NetworkLinks are linked to Resources and managed by Agents.
# All Applications are linked to ApplicationModules and have type/importance.
# All ApplicationModules are linked to Applications, managed by Teams/Agents, and have status/SLA.
# All Services are linked to ApplicationModules/Applications.
# All TroubleTickets are linked to Services/Applications/Resources, Parties, and triggered by EventRecords.
# All ChangeRequests are linked to impacted entities, Parties, and have status/cause.
# All EventRecords are linked to ManagedObjects, ManagementSystems, and sometimes Agents.
# All KOS concepts are defined.
# All entities have labels and comments.
# No ldp prefix used.
# The number of entities and triples should be sufficient for the token count.
# The graph is highly interconnected.
